sec.p:
From 2004 to 2009, the mean annual laying date of early breeders did not affect annual sex ratio at fledging (GLM; 
  z = −0.02, 
  P = 0.99). Similarly, the mean annual breeding success of the colony over the 10-year study (2000–2009) was not related to fledgling sex ratio (GLM; 
  z = 1.07, 
  P = 0.28).
